#. translators: %s: theme name.
#: inc/admin.php:225
#, php-format
msgid "%s is a free, full-site-editing theme built to get out of the way of your content. Here is how to make it yours."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:239
msgid "Choose what people land on."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:240
msgid "A visitor's first second decides whether they stay. Set a static front page under Settings → Reading, and give your posts a page of their own."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:243
msgid "Give people a way around."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:244
msgid "A site without a menu is a room without doors. Open the Site Editor, edit the header, and assign your menu to Primary Navigation."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:247
msgid "Start from a pattern, not a blank page."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:248
msgid "In any page or post, open the block inserter, choose Patterns, and find this theme's group. Drop one in and change the words."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:251
msgid "Make it sound like you."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:252
msgid "In the Site Editor, open Styles to change colours and typefaces. Nothing you do there can break the theme — experiment freely."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:256
msgid "This theme is fast by design: reading is JavaScript-free (only the breaking-news dismiss control ships a small script), self-hosted fonts that don't phone home, and tuning against the Core Web Vitals search engines actually measure."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:257
msgid "It is built to WCAG 2.2 AA guidance — real focus outlines, a skip link, sensible heading order, and motion that respects a reduce-motion setting. Keep your own copy and images to that bar and the whole site stays welcoming."
msgstr ""

#: inc/admin.php:259
msgid "There's a small credit in your footer. It's a thank-you, not a tax — remove it in two clicks in the Site Editor → Footer, or filter it out in code. No hard feelings either way."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: linked developer-guide anchor.
